BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:c69fa1b9-bf8e-592d-a351-81da5fd3e912
DTSTAMP:20260319T145240Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260418T153000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260418T163000
SUMMARY:Austin Pediatric Echo Conference
LOCATION:Dell Children’s Medical Center\, Signe Auditorium
DESCRIPTION:The Austin Pediatric Echo Conference brings together leading pe
 diatric and neonatal echocardiography specialists to deliver a focused\, h
 ands-on introduction to imaging the developing heart. Attendees learn prac
 tical scanning skills\, understand key differences between pediatric and a
 dult echo and observe live demonstrations from experts in congenital heart
  disease and advanced cardiac imaging. This one-day program is designed to
  strengthen confidence\, deepen clinical insight and provide immediately a
 pplicable skills for frontline providers. The experience emphasizes real-w
 orld application\, collaborative learning\, and direct mentorship from spe
 cialists at the Texas Center for Pediatric and Congenital Heart Disease\, 
 a clinical partnership between UT Health Austin and Dell Children’s Medica
 l Center. The conference is intended for: Pediatric residents exploring ca
 rdiology Neonatologists Adult echo technologists expanding into pediatric 
 imaging Advanced practice providers PICU providers seeking stronger echo p
 roficiency Sandhya Ramlogan \, MBChB\, presents the keynote address. Ramlo
 gan is a board-certified pediatric cardiologist and medical director of th
 e Echocardiography Laboratory at the Texas Center for Pediatric and Congen
 ital Heart Disease. She is also an associate professor in the Department o
 f Pediatrics at Dell Med. For more information\, email Sofia Hobbs . Upon 
 request\, Dell Med will provide interpretation services at this event. Ple
 ase notify Sofia by April 3\, 2026\, if interpretation is needed.\\n\\nEve
 nt page: https://dellmed.utexas.edu/events/austin-pediatric-echo-conferenc
 e-041826
URL:https://dellmed.utexas.edu/events/austin-pediatric-echo-conference-0418
 26
END:VEVENT
